    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Internally, network settings are stored at `~/.brownie/network-config.yaml`.  For development networks, all ganache related flags are in the `cmd_settings` field.\r\n\r\nSome of the existing fields, and the new field proposed in this issue, are definitely project-dependent. I think the best approach is to expose `cmd_settings` within `brownie-config.yaml`, something like this:\r\n\r\n```yaml\r\nnetworks:\r\n    default: development\r\n    development:\r\n        cmd_settings:\r\n            block_time: 10\r\n            default_balance: \"1000 ether\"\r\n```",
